            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@Mycotina It&apos;s easier to understand when you think of the instruction pipeline cache as tracks, the train (with cars) as the instructions, and the indicator of whether you go left or right by some dude at the END of the train; not the beginning. By the time you see him to know you&apos;ve guessed right, not only is it too late to switch things, the pipeline ahead is already populated, but in the wrong direction. If you guessed wrong the predicted pipeline needs to be thrown out (derail the train; drag it back before the switch house, put it back on the tracks, and send it the other way).&lt;/span&gt;

