            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@C.Binair Primarily it&apos;s runtime, i.e. processor predicts branches while executing the code. The processor also remembers previous results and use that to predict next jump. However, compiler can provide some initial hints for branch prediction while compiling - search for &quot;likely&quot; and &quot;unlikely&quot; attributes. So you could say the answer is kinda both, but runtime is when it actually happens.&lt;/span&gt;

