            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@MooingDuck To a human eye, &quot;TTFFTTFFTTFF&quot; is a predictable sequence, but what we are talking about here is the behavior of the branch predictor built into a CPU.  The branch predictor is not AI-level pattern recognition; it&apos;s very simple.  When you just alternate branches it doesn&apos;t predict well.  In most code, branches go the same way almost all the time; consider a loop that executes a thousand times.  The branch at the end of the loop goes back to the start of the loop 999 times, and then the thousandth time does something different.  A very simple branch predictor works well, usually.&lt;/span&gt;

