            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@mckenzm: out-of-order speculative exec makes branch prediction even more valuable; as well as hiding fetch/decode bubbles, branch prediction + speculative exec removes control dependencies from critical path latency.  Code inside or after an &lt;code&gt;if()&lt;/code&gt; block can execute &lt;i&gt;before&lt;/i&gt; the branch condition is known.  Or for a search loop like &lt;code&gt;strlen&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;memchr&lt;/code&gt;, interations can overlap.  If you had to wait for the match-or-not result to be known before running any of the next iteration, you&apos;d bottleneck on cache load + ALU latency instead of throughput.&lt;/span&gt;

